values:
I&#39;ve done that thing again where I had an excellnt idea for a blog post, only I didn&#39;t write it down. Oops. Should have done that, because apparently, my brain seems to have a finite capacity to hold stuff in it. Not that I&#39;m surprised by this, actually. I&#39;ve known it for a long &nbsp;time and just learned to live with teh consequences of things falling out.&nbsp;

Anyway, snce I really don&#39;t have a lot to say, I thought I would point you in the direction of Kage Alan&#39;s blog because I found this post highly entertaining. It&#39;s his take on people getting what they want and how they go about it. T<a href="http://www.kagealan.com/blog/2012/these-over-those-your-feminine-wiles-have-no-effect-on-me/" target="_blank">hese over Those: Your Feminin Wiles Have No Effect on Me</a>&nbsp; I would encourage you to poke arunf his blog some. Its one of the few I read on a regular basis, because no matter what he&#39;s talking about, he finds a way to make it entertaining and enjoyable.&nbsp;

Also, because I particularly like this drawing, I thought I might share.&nbsp;<a href="http://dontkickmycane.livejournal.com/pics/catalog/1196/40016" target="_blank"><img alt="damian sleeping" height="355" src="http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/dontkickmycane/8880955/40016/40016_original.jpg" style="border-width: 5px; margin: 10px; " title="damian sleeping" width="726" /></a>
